It is possible to create a web proxy using HTML, JavaScript, AJAX, jQuery, and PHP. Here are some general steps to help you get started:

1. Create an HTML form that takes a URL input from the user.
2. Use JavaScript to get the URL input and make an AJAX request to your PHP script.
3. In the PHP script, create a cURL request to the requested URL.
4. Use the cURL response to generate the response for your proxy server.
5. Use PHP to output the response.

Here is an example code that demonstrates some of the basic concepts of a web proxy:

HTML:
```
<form id="proxyForm">
  <input type="text" id="urlInput" placeholder="Enter a URL">
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
<div id="responseArea"></div>
```

JavaScript/jQuery:
```
$('#proxyForm').submit(function(event) {
  event.preventDefault();
  var url = $('#urlInput').val();
  $.ajax({
    type: 'GET',
    url: '/proxy.php',
    data: {url: url},
    success: function(response) {
      $('#responseArea').html(response);
    }
  });
});
```

PHP (proxy.php):
```
<?php
if(isset($_GET['url'])) {
  $url = $_GET['url'];

  $curl = curl_init($url);
  curl_setopt($curl, CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER, true);
  $response = curl_exec($curl);
  curl_close($curl);

  echo $response;
}
?>
```

Note that this code is a basic example and may not handle all types of URLs or requests. Additionally, creating a web proxy can have legal and ethical implications, so use caution when creating one and ensure that you are using it responsibly and legally.
